I have updated the files in the CVS repository to fix the memory leak 
in the multiphase equilibrium solver, and to implement several other 
relatively minor changes.  This updated version works fine on Mac and 
linux, but there seems to be some problem on Windows that causes some, 
but not all, example m-files in MATLAB to fail.  I haven't had time to 
track it down yet.  For this reason, I have not posted a new Windows 
installer.

I'm going to be out of town through the 28th, and out of email contact. 
  I'll get back to this when i return, but if any Windows/MATLAB expert 
wants to tackle it in the meantime, you are most welcome to do so...

Dave
